The search for Sheba the tiger continues. Walkerville community members are now afraid to go about their daily activities. eNCA's Moloko Moloto has more details. #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - A Johannesburg South man mauled by a tiger has gone the legal route. The 39-year-old is suing the owner of the female tiger, that attacked him and a dog on Saturday night in the Walkerville area. WACH | Female tiger on the loose south of Johannesburg The animal escaped from its cage and is still on the loose. Meanwhile, the man is in hospital receiving medical attention. The lawyer for the injured man spoke to reporter Moloko Moloto. 